#Step 6 - DC01 (Domain Controller)

I will now work on my DC, I will need DNS and AD roles and I might go over DHCP too but my DHCP is handled by the FortiGate VM. I might switch back and forth just for practice.

1. Network config:
- Static IP: 10.0.0.10
- Subnet mask: 255.255.255.0 (/24)
- Default gateway: 10.0.0.1 (FGT01)
- Prefered DNS: 10.0.0.10
- Disabled IPv6

Tested ping to FGT01 - working.

2. Roles:
- Add roles and features > Active Directory Domain Services + DNS Server

3. Promoted server to domain controller:
- New forest: corp.lab
- NetBIOS name: CORPLAB
- Set DSRM password
- Pre-requisites installed automatically
- Went through full install and reboot, verified AD and DNS are up and correct.

4. FortiGate config and DNS forwarder:
- Setup DC01 to forward to 8.8.8.8 (DNS Manager > Properties > Forwarders > added 8.8.8.8)
- Went through FortiGate config:
  - config firewall policy
  - edit 2
  - set name "VLAN2_to_VLAN1_AD"
  - set srcintf port3
  - set dstintf port2
  - set srcaddr all
  - set dstaddr all
  - set action accept
  - set schedule always
  - set service DNS LDAP KERBEROS SMB
  - next
  - end
- Tested ping from WIN10-01 to 10.0.0.10 and nslookup corp.lab - works

DC01 has now a solid foudnational setup and ping works between clients to DC01 from a different subnet, will continue later.
